c classes since they can still be public members. I'm also considering the implications for a DocumentId public field in a package-private class, which might raise exceptions if not handled correctly. \\n\\nIt could be beneficial to create public static helper classes inside the test to avoid excessively naming them, but then there's the risk of violating the rule about test files. Making one helper class public could be a good compromise for managing public fields and methods.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Verifying method accessibility in Java**\\n\\nI'm thinking about testing things quickly with jshell, but the guidelines suggest not to compile or run tests. I recall that `Class.getMethods()` includes public members of non-public classes, such as the package-private `Arrays$ArrayList`, which has public methods. While it seems like it should return public methods, reflection can fail without setAccessible due to class visibility issues. \\n\\nI’m also considering a potential issue with `CustomClassMapper.convertToPlainJavaTypes` regarding the mapper cache— since the execution order can be unpredictable. However, distinct classes should help keep things manageable.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_8bgcPJ8ZBW4plRdoFGX1eFOW|fc_0e16c4517a93d10c0169f77d67ee00819f8a6b2ac494f2d84b", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "rg -n \"void close|shutdownNow|shutdown\" /home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/source_context/com.google.cloud/google-cloud-firestore/3.31.6/main/extracted/com/google/cloud/firestore/spi/v1/GrpcFirestoreRpc.java | head -80", "timeout": 30}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 11918, "output": 900, "cacheRead": 40960, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 53778, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777827159688, "responseId": "resp_0e16c4517a93d10c0169f77d584